NAME
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            update - flush graphics

SYNOPSIS
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            update ?options?

DESCRIPTION
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            Changes made via Tk commands do not become visible until a
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            call to update. Update flushes any pending changes to the
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            screen. The following options are supported:

<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            -disable
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>                 If this option is given, all updates are disabled. This
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>                 is useful to enable a program to stop mouse movement
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>                 causing automatic updates while it is making changes to
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>                 the window.

<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            -enable
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>                 This reverses a previous update -enable invocation.

BUGS
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            Changes that affect window sizes are visible immediately.

<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>                                Inferno Manual
